                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">19th-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <desc>Fine and regular.
                       The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line on, e.g. <locus target="#31r #117r #135r #143v #156r"/>. 
                       The scribe used compressed script: <locus target="#10r"/>.
                       Part of the line is taken up on, e.g., <locus target="#24v #42v #110r #154r"/>. 
                       Part of the line is taken down on, e.g., <locus target="#28v #33r #48v #76r #101v #120v"/>.</desc> 
                        
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>Abbreviations in <ref target="#ms_i1.1"/>
                           <list>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>እስመ፡ / እስመ፡ ለዓ፡/ እስመ፡ ምሕረቱ፡/ እስመ፡ ለዓለምረቱ፡, etc.</abbr> for
                              <expan>እስመ፡ ለዓለም፡ ምሕረቱ፡</expan> (Ps. 135 <locus target="#123r #123v"/>)</item>
                              <item>Abbreviations in <ref target="#ms_i1.2"/></item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ስቡ፡ / ስቡሕኒ፡</abbr> for <expan>ስቡሕኒ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወልዑልኒ፡ ውእቱ፡  ለዓለም፡</expan>፡
                              (Canticle 10 <locus target="#144v #145r #145v"/>)</item>
                           </list>
